             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a waiter at George's coffee-house. On the 31st of March the prisoner came in, and asked me what soup I had: I told him; and he desired me to bring him a bason, which I did, and gave him a silver spoon to eat it with; I did not see him go away: I saw him at Bow-street the Saturday following.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17910413-51-verdict291" type="verdictDescription">
